<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Combs</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-02"><hi rend="italic">June 2,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Combs says he has been requested by the Guatemalan minister for
                            foreign affairs to report that 250 armed men, of whose character he is
                            not sure, entered Guatemala from Salvador, but that no collision has yet
                            taken place. Mr. Combs has urged self-restraint in strong terms.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>